<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,577,926]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,577,602]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the smallest of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[571,695,578,601]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[571,695,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known to 
<collectingRegion box="[903,992,578,601]" country="Panama" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<collectingCountry box="[903,992,578,601]" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Panama</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
with body lengths of about 
<quantity box="[1309,1389,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
and wing spans less than 
<quantity box="[407,494,614,638]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 mm</quantity>
. The green head and thorax marked with piceous with a piceous abdomen, the postclypeus not extending anteriorly beyond the supra-antennal plates when viewed from the dorsal side and the fore wings lacking infuscation on the radial and radiomedial crossveins which easily distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1850" box="[1318,1405,686,709]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Fidicina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aper">
<emphasis box="[1318,1405,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">M. aper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
